# Backend — {{ project_name }}

Spring Boot 4 (Kotlin 2.2+, Java 21) backend service.

## Quick Reference

- **Build**: `./gradlew build` (or `gradlew.bat build` on Windows)
- **Run**: `./gradlew bootRun`
- **Test**: `./gradlew test`
- **Port**: 8080 (configurable via `PORT` env var)

## Architecture

```
src/main/kotlin/{{ package_identifier | replace('.', '/') }}/
  config/          → Security, CORS, OAuth2
  common/          → Shared models, exceptions, error handler
  auth/            → Authentication (OAuth + {% if "password" in auth_methods %}password + {% endif %}JWT)
  features/        → Feature modules (controller → service → repository)
```

## Conventions

- **Package per feature**: each feature in `features/{name}/` with controller, service, repository, model subpackages
- **DTOs**: separate request/response data classes, never expose entities
- **Exceptions**: throw `ApiException` subclasses — `GlobalExceptionHandler` maps to JSON
- **Auth**: JWT Bearer token; `@AuthenticationPrincipal user: User` in controllers
- **Migrations**: Flyway in `resources/db/migration/V{N}__{description}.sql`
- **Tests**: `@SpringBootTest` + `@ActiveProfiles("test")` with H2 in-memory DB

## Key Files

- `config/SecurityConfig.kt` — endpoint security rules, JWT filter
- `config/OAuth2Config.kt` — OAuth provider credentials
- `auth/security/JwtTokenProvider.kt` — token generation/validation
- `application.yml` — all configuration (DB, JWT, OAuth, CORS)
- `resources/db/migration/V1__init.sql` — initial schema

